Dear Members of the General Court:
I am pleased to submit this Report to the Legislature: Recovery High School Programs
Legislative Report – Fiscal Year 2023. As required by the statute, the enclosed report
includes: “(i) the number of youths served per high school; (ii) outcomes measured for
youths; and (iii) recommendations for new recovery high schools in fiscal year 2023 and
fiscal year 2024.” The data provided in this report was compiled from information
submitted by schools to the Massachusetts Department of Elementary and Secondary
Education (Department).
For adolescents in recovery from a substance use disorder, school is a setting that may
result in interactions with peer groups who are actively using alcohol or other drugs.
Unfortunately, after treatment, these students may encounter multiple risk factors when
returning to the setting where their substance use problems originated. Recovery High
School programs play an important role for these students by offering them another option
for a school setting – one in which they can feel supported in their recovery while still
working towards a high school diploma.
